  "title": {
    "@language": "en",
    "@value": "Periorificial dermatitis"
  },
  "definition": {
    "@language": "en",
    "@value": "Periorificial dermatitis is a term which links two erythematous and papulopustular facial dermatoses that are strongly linked to prolonged potent topical corticosteroid use, namely perioral dermatitis and periocular dermatitis. It is characterised by the development of erythema, papules and pustules in perioral and periocular skin."
